hZ.HuHgAk-/0/1740022211609?e=1778112000&v=beta&t=ZcWogAlEXUXXF_cdTnGZMqHHnIqD9oFkUlsZSk3xkuM", "peopleAlsoViewed/25/public_identifier": "sebastien-lalanne-aa55731b5", "peopleAlsoViewed/25/url": "https://linkedin.com/in/ACoAADIYXV0B1LIz_mBmcOo8hsGvJQV6fDo89Fw", "profilePic": "https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/D4E03AQHyX68PF6C8Rw/profile-displayphoto-shrink_800_800/profile-displayphoto-shrink_800_800/0/1695359184674?e=1778112000&v=beta&t=HoUkERgcefUBHqVPSl7KO9ZagOkA12bdLgK93wo2Vag", "profilePicHighQuality": "https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/D4E03AQHyX68PF6C8Rw/profile-displayphoto-shrink_800_800/profile-displayphoto-shrink_800_800/0/1695359184674?e=1778112000&v=beta&t=HoUkERgcefUBHqVPSl7KO9ZagOkA12bdLgK93wo2Vag", "publicIdentifier": "albertvanderwesthuizen", "recommendations/0/context": "Albert managed Sarun directly", "recommendations/0/date": "June 18, 2025", "recommendations/0/description": "I have had the pleasure of working with James in both his current role as Brand Manager and previously as an Assistant. \n\nThroughout this time, he has consistently demonstrated outstanding determination, a strong work ethic, and an impressive ability to adapt quickly to new challenges.\n\nJames has a keen eye for graphic design, often delivering high-quality creative assets under tight deadlines. \n\nHis talent in this area has elevated the visual identity of our brand significantly. Additionally, he has shown great initiative and professionalism in managing our relationship with an outsourced PR agency, often catching and correcting their errors to ensure our communications remained polished and on-brand.\n\nHe is a reliable and proactive team member, and I would highly recommend him for any future opportunities.", "recommendations/0/name": "Sarun SINTHUSART", "recommendations/0/subtitle": "Creative Manager | Content Strategy · Brand Building · Creative Direction | Helping Thai digital audiences discover stories worth sharing", "recommendations/0/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/sarun-sinthusart/", "recommendations/0/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAB6JYmQBjEPbiND-OaBHGWSwAleUyW37pvk", "recommendations/1/context": "Albert managed Sebastien directly", "recommendations/1/date": "April 16, 2025", "recommendations/1/description": "Chef Sebastien is an exceptional Executive Chef I had the privilege of working with on the launch of several successful restaurant concepts.\n\nSebastien was a key player in every aspect of our openings—from concept development and menu creation to staff training and execution. His culinary creativity, operational expertise, and leadership were vital to our success.\n\nChef had a rare ability to balance innovation with practicality, bringing bold ideas to life while keeping teams focused and efficient. Just as impressive is his ability to inspire those around them, fostering a culture of excellence and collaboration.\n\nI highly recommend Chef Sebastien for any leadership role in the culinary field. They’re a true professional and a tremendous asset to any team.", "recommendations/1/name": "Sebastien LALANNE", "recommendations/1/subtitle": "Corporate Chef", "recommendations/1/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/sebastien-lalanne-aa55731b5/", "recommendations/1/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAADIYXV0B1LIz_mBmcOo8hsGvJQV6fDo89Fw", "recommendations/2/context": "Albert worked with Danielle on the same team", "recommendations/2/date": "July 22, 2020", "recommendations/2/description": "I’ve known Danielle in a professional capacity for a number of years after being colleagues in the luxury super yacht industry in Florida and later when she was working for a notable executive chef and restaurateur in New York City. \n\nDanielle was responsible for designing guest experiences for high profile and VIP clientele, event execution, spa experiences and the financial performance of the businesses she managed. \n\nI have on many occasions witnessed her ability to deliver on multiple priorities on time, on budget and to intuitively anticipate customers needs, a skill which saw her build repeat business for both the yachting and hospitality roles she held. She is highly organised and has a keen eye for detail which means she creates perfectly executed events and doesn’t compromise on quality, much to the delight of guests. \n\nWith Danielle’s skill in business development and her ability to relate to people from all walks of life, I would not hesitate to add her to my team if ever I had the opportunity. I know she will be successful in any role she undertakes requiring these skills. ", "recommendations/2/name": "Danielle Williams", "recommendations/2/subtitle": "Strategic Business Development | B2B/B2C Sales | Medical Aesthetics | Clinical Education | Luxury Spa & Wellness | Leadership | Learning & Development", "recommendations/2/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/danielle-williams-67919226/", "recommendations/2/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAVdlj0Bf_KzF3DOoYRZCHwoz1oW-mEaxJ0", "recommendations/3/context": "Albert reported directly to Edmund", "recommendations/3/date": "July 10, 2020", "recommendations/3/description": "Edmund is wonderful to work with, and has exceptional expertise in leadership, coaching & motivation. He consistently demonstrated a solid work ethic plus a dedication to success. Edmund is dedicated, self-motivated and very capable. He is not only a reliable and forward thinking individual but also an inspiring team player. Would work with him again.  ", "recommendations/3/name": "Edmund Lowman", "recommendations/3/subtitle": "Entrepreneur and Investor", "recommendations/3/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/edmund-lowman-984923156/", "recommendations/3/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAACWDB7QBoPQ8OFkwWIOjLAp5hhbv8tj-bzg", "recommendations/4/context": "Albert managed Edina directly", "recommendations/4/date": "November 3, 2016", "recommendations/4/description": "I've worked with Edina more then 3 years at a time where the Chino Latino brand was rapidly growing and we were expanding into Europe and won a Catey Award for Restaurant Team of the Year 2011.. Edina started in the bar, worked her way around the restaurant and then became my ever so reliable and loyal coordinator. Edina is dedicated, passionate but also very creative and a girl with no limitations when it comes to service. She will do what ever it takes to make anything happen with her positive demeanour. I've recommended and supported Edina's very first F&B Manager role and also her new General Manager role. If I could I would work with her in a heart beat because working 'horses with hearts' like Edina is very hard to find. I wish her all the best and I know one day we will work together again. ", "recommendations/4/name": "Edina Sipocz", "recommendations/4/subtitle": "Lifestyle Manager", "recommendations/4/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/edina-sipocz/", "recommendations/4/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAB1n0XABZOkwhgv4_Z4hSU0n6vvJpylssUU", "recommendations/5/context": "Albert worked with Vickita on the same team", "recommendations/5/date": "October 22, 2014", "recommendations/5/description": "Vickita is very creative, highly organised, manages all strategic and tactical Marketing and Brand activity, including managing the hotel's creative agency, and is commercially accountable for the Marketing budget. Working with the GM to identify ways to increase revenue and grow the business through clever and cutting edge marketing activity, Vickita always puts the brand and business first and would never compromise the brand experience for short term wins. Vickita is not only all the above but she is always true, honest and very hands on and will never turn her back on any challenge, it was an honour to work alongside Vickita.", "recommendations/5/name": "Vickita Reddy", "recommendations/5/subtitle": "Head of Marketing & Communications", "recommendations/5/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/vickitareddy/", "recommendations/5/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAGtb98Bg8Y95Ydx9Wx9wJtizHJcbymNCY0", "recommendations/6/context": "Albert was senior to Aline but didn't manage Aline directly", "recommendations/6/date": "August 7, 2013", "recommendations/6/description": "During the time I’ve worked with Aline she has always been courteous, dedicated and trustworthy, acting in a mature manner at all times. Hotel guest’s and other Head of Departments find her approachable and a great team player who always assisted where possible.\n\nAline’s creativity, passionate approach and inspirational leadership skills has been a great asset and support to my Team and hers during my time at The Arch London Hotel. \n\nI would have no hesitation in recommending Aline to any future employee, in fact I would be very honoured to every have the chance to work with her again.", "recommendations/6/name": "Aline K.", "recommendations/6/subtitle": "#motivated #committed #opportunities #backontrack #readyforchange", "recommendations/6/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/aline-k-614b7238/", "recommendations/6/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAgAy_AB_lXnL5uFppY0rfv0uMQnEzWPU6s", "recommendations/7/context": "Albert worked with Richi on the same team", "recommendations/7/date": "February 9, 2013", "recommendations/7/description": "During my time at Chino Latino we never got it right with the \"perfect\" HR Manager. Then Richi turned up and what a difference she made, not only in HR but also operationally. Richi cared, Richi was passionate and made time for every employee no matter what. In all my time in London I've never had the opportunity to meet such a professional and engaging individual. Richi made us believed that the impossible was possible and to take one day at a time was a positive achievement. Sometimes we forgot about the people who made us achieve our dreams but Richi never made us forget who we were. If I can work with Richi again I would be blessed in many ways. Not only was she a great leader but also a great support to all.", "recommendations/7/name": "Richi Kukreja", "recommendations/7/subtitle": "Director, HR Business Partner, Zoetis UK", "recommendations/7/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/richi-kukreja-1969658/", "recommendations/7/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAGQtMIBD9Zs6dV1Ud_Iv3Y5CH_gs96UDNE", "recommendations/8/context": "Albert was Tryphena's client", "recommendations/8/date": "February 9, 2013", "recommendations/8/description": "During my time as the Brand Manager of Chino Latino, Tryphena was our Account Manager and what a joy to work with. Tryphena did not only gave us \"out side the box\" ideas on how to improve our image but also shown creativity and support putting Chino Latino on the map. In the past I've worked with many PR individuals but never with someone so engaging wanting to achieve only the highest standards and achievements. If I get the opportunity to work with her again I will do so in a hear beat.", "recommendations/8/name": "Tryphena Greenwood", "recommendations/8/subtitle": "Communications and PR - GCC & UK expertise", "recommendations/8/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/tryphena-greenwood-b4561a9/", "recommendations/8/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAGxcuUBuCDsqPhAPWmUwwk5qAZYs8jcIPo", "recommendationsReceived/0/context": "Benwin worked with Albert on the same team", "recommendationsReceived/0/date": "October 9, 2025", "recommendationsReceived/0/description": "I’ve had the privilege of working alongside Albert and I can confidently say that he exemplifies the rare blend of visionary leadership, and the hands on execution. Weather shaping long-term strategy or rolling up his sleeves to solve complex challenges, Albert consistently demonstrates a deep understanding of all the big picture and the operational details. \nAs a true culture builder, Albert Fosters environments where teams feel empowered, engaged and aligned around the shared purpose. His ability to cultivate trust and drive collaboration has been instrumental in building high-performing, values driven teams. \nCommercially, sharp and relentlessly focused on delivering results, Albert brings strategic lens to every decision – balancing innovation, and pragmatism. His guest obsession is evident in every touch point, ensuring that customer experience is not just a metric, but a mindset embedded across the organization. \nEqually impressive is Albert‘s commitment to sustainability. He approach business with long-term view, championing initiatives that are both environmentally, responsible and commercially viable. \nIn high pressure situations, Albert remains calm, decisive, and solutions oriented, bringing clarity and confidence when it’s needed most. His relationship driven approach both internally and externally has built enduring partnerships and a strong network of advocates.\nIn short, Albert is transformative leader whose impact has felt across people performance and purpose. Any organization would be fortunate to have him at the helm.", "recommendationsReceived/0/name": "Benwin Thomas", "recommendationsReceived/0/subtitle": "Facilities Manager", "recommendationsReceived/0/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/benwin-thomas-8416221b3/", "recommendationsReceived/0/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAADG_bDEBYg43XSf7CE8-orEqQa7QbPNi29A", "recommendationsReceived/1/context": "Sarun reported directly to Albert", "recommendationsReceived/1/date": "June 14, 2025", "recommendationsReceived/1/description": "I had the opportunity to work under Albert’s supervision and learned a great deal from his leadership. He’s highly determined and consistently gets things done, even under pressure.\n\nOne of the things I respect most about Albert is his approach to problem-solving—he doesn’t hand you the answers, but instead encourages you to think independently and come to your own conclusions. It’s a leadership style that builds confidence and capability within the team.\n\nWith his solid background in hospitality, Albert knows the ins and outs of the industry. His creative direction is sharp, and his attention to detail sets a clear standard. He leads by example, which makes it easy for the team to follow suit and grow through observation.\n\nWhile he maintains high standards and can be strict when needed, he balances it with empathy and kindness. This combination creates a positive work environment and helps maintain strong team morale.\n\nAlbert is someone who earns respect through action, not just words—and that’s what makes him a strong leader.", "recommendationsReceived/1/name": "Sarun SINTHUSART", "recommendationsReceived/1/subtitle": "Creative Manager | Content Strategy · Brand Building · Creative Direction | Helping Thai digital audiences discover stories worth sharing", "recommendationsReceived/1/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/sarun-sinthusart/", "recommendationsReceived/1/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAB6JYmQBjEPbiND-OaBHGWSwAleUyW37pvk", "recommendationsReceived/2/context": "Jodi reported directly to Albert", "recommendationsReceived/2/date": "June 2, 2025", "recommendationsReceived/2/description": "It’s not every day you come across a leader who truly changes the course of your career — and your life. I had the incredible privilege of working under Albert as my General Manager, and to this day, I can say without hesitation: he was the best leader I’ve ever had in hospitality.\n\nFrom day one, he saw potential in me that I hadn’t yet recognized in myself. He didn’t let me settle for “comfortable” — instead, he pushed me, challenged me, and believed in me in moments when I doubted myself. Thanks to his mentorship, I grew not only as a manager but as a person. If it weren’t for him, I’d probably still be five years behind in my career.\n\nHe gave me opportunities I never dreamed of — including the chance to travel the world, take on new roles, and experience the industry from a global perspective. Each experience was a lesson, and each lesson was a step toward becoming the best version of myself professionally.\n\nAlbert, thank you for being the kind of leader who leads with integrity, vision, and heart. Your impact on my career will stay with me forever.", "recommendationsReceived/2/name": "Jodi Gillespie", "recommendationsReceived/2/subtitle": "Executive Chef of Waterfront Properties", "recommendationsReceived/2/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/jlgillespie/", "recommendationsReceived/2/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAtGLGQBgiFM8Ff10926h05ElLO5pQbM8wQ", "recommendationsReceived/3/context": "Sebastien reported directly to Albert", "recommendationsReceived/3/date": "April 22, 2025", "recommendationsReceived/3/description": "I had the pleasure of working with Albert from December 2023 to March 2025, during which he served as our Managing Director. From the very beginning, Albert brought strong leadership and a clear vision to the table.\n\nHe played a key role in getting our restaurants up and running with impressive efficiency and organization. One of the things I appreciated most was how he structured our work—everyone had well-defined tasks, and we held weekly meetings to share progress and get feedback. This clear rhythm helped the whole team stay on track and feel supported.\n\nAlbert’s leadership created a productive and positive work environment, and I’m grateful for the experience of working with him.", "recommendationsReceived/3/name": "Sebastien LALANNE", "recommendationsReceived/3/subtitle": "Corporate Chef", "recommendationsReceived/3/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/sebastien-lalanne-aa55731b5/", "recommendationsReceived/3/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAADIYXV0B1LIz_mBmcOo8hsGvJQV6fDo89Fw", "recommendationsReceived/4/context": "Audrey worked with Albert but on different teams", "recommendationsReceived/4/date": "April 30, 2021", "recommendationsReceived/4/description": "Albert and I worked together in Ho Chi Minh on the opening of a beautiful and   select lounge. It was  a very short  mission and I regret it has been so short. I still had the chance to see the amazing training and motivating skills of Albert with his staff. He is also incredibly precise, paying attention on every little details. He was not counting his hours until the Grand Opening and it paid off! I hope our path will cross again in the future. ", "recommendationsReceived/4/name": "Audrey Pravata", "recommendationsReceived/4/subtitle": "🔹️ Master in F&B Management Rome Business School🔹️Meetings Support🔹️Instructor 🔹️Restaurant & Cooking Studio Owner and a very HAPPY and POSITIVE girl!", "recommendationsReceived/4/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/audrey-pravata-a74a8140/", "recommendationsReceived/4/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAizjLgBvloZGilxOsLXCDrLsoxRyKAiivY", "recommendationsReceived/5/context": "Matthew managed Albert directly", "recommendationsReceived/5/date": "December 8, 2020", "recommendationsReceived/5/description": "I had the pleasure in 2019, when I was consulted to Destination Eats, to work with one Albert who was one of of our Director of Operations, an out of the box thinker and inspirational manager to his staff and peers.  He challenged the team every day to better than the day before, he was an asset to the business and would be an asset to anyone who was fortunate work with him in the future. ", "recommendationsReceived/5/name": "Matthew Putna", "recommendationsReceived/5/subtitle": "Business & Commercial Sales, Asian Franchise Consultant, Retired", "recommendationsReceived/5/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/matthew-putna-b8191721/", "recommendationsReceived/5/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAASVwtEBeGdvDPeJ8QfUL5e7GACxpdHX_CQ", "recommendationsReceived/6/context": "Christian worked with Albert on the same team", "recommendationsReceived/6/date": "September 3, 2020", "recommendationsReceived/6/description": "Albert is result driven, with a keen eye for detail and have the practical leadership skills to make things happen, he has a proven track record in successfully launching a number of impressive projects internationally over the years. \n\nHe understand the importance of establi